<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/foce/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.12: Nested Conditionals</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.12</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">Nested Conditionals</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>Nesting</p>
              <p>pass</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Nesting</h2>
              <p>
                An <code>if</code> statement can go inside another
                <code>if</code> statement's block. This is called
                <b class="text-sn-theme">nesting</b> &mdash; the inner
                decision only happens if the outer condition was true first.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure1} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Nesting</h2>
              <Code code={Figure2} frame="terminal" lang="txt" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>pass</h2>
              <p>
                Python can't have a truly empty indented block &mdash; if
                you want to sketch out a structure before filling it in,
                <b class="text-sn-theme">pass</b> is a placeholder that does
                nothing.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure3} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Today's Project: Dungeon Crawler</h2>
              <p>
                A choose-your-own-adventure story, built one branch at a
                time &mdash; starting with an empty skeleton of nested
                <code>if</code>/<code>elif</code>/<code>else</code> blocks,
                filled in one path at a time.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Nesting an <code>if</code> statement inside another</li>
                <li>Sketching a decision structure with <code>pass</code> before filling it in</li>
                <li>Tracking a story's state with boolean and numeric variables</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>Nesting</dt>
                  <dd>Placing one code block (like an <code>if</code>) inside another.</dd>
                  <dt>pass</dt>
                  <dd>A placeholder statement that does nothing &mdash; used where Python requires a block but you have nothing to put there yet.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new Python script named <b class="text-sn-theme">1-12-dungeon-crawler.py</b>. You'll build this story one branch at a time.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Set Up Your Variables</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Declare the ending flags, gold, and twinkies &mdash; all start false or zero.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task1} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-12-dungeon-crawler.py" mark="2-5" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: The Prologue</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Set the scene, then ask the player which path they take.</li>
            <li>If they chose a real path, offer them the Twinkie.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task2} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-12-dungeon-crawler.py" mark="15,19" ins="7-27" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 3: Sketch the Cave Branches</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Add an <code>if</code>/<code>elif</code>/<code>else</code> for
              the left path, right path, and no-path-chosen case &mdash;
              using <code>pass</code> to leave each one empty for now.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task3} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-12-dungeon-crawler.py" mark="33-38" ins="29-38" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 4: The Wolfpack Path</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Fill in the left path &mdash; the player meets a wolf pack, and the Twinkie changes the outcome.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task4} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-12-dungeon-crawler.py" mark="34-51" ins="34-51" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 5: The Dragon Path</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Fill in the right path &mdash; the player meets a dragon and can choose how much gold to take.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task5} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-12-dungeon-crawler.py" mark="52-78" ins="52-78" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 6: No Path Chosen</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Fill in what happens if the player never picked left or right.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task6} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-12-dungeon-crawler.py" mark="80-81" ins="80-81" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 7: The Epilogue</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Print an ending based on which boolean flags got set to <code>True</code>.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task7} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-12-dungeon-crawler.py" mark="86-95,97-98" ins="83-98" />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={SampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>Why did the wolf pack and dragon branches need to be nested inside the left/right path check, instead of being separate standalone <code>if</code> statements?</li>
            <li>What would have happened if you tried to leave the cave branches truly empty in Task 3, without <code>pass</code>?</li>
            <li>How do the two ending boolean flags decide which epilogue message prints?</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
